I guess the problem is in Wrapper.java,
Wrapper.java generates the function in the invokeMethod that iterates over the method list of the provider 
 interface. When the method name is not included in the provider interface, it throws com.alibaba.dubbo.common.bytecode.NoSuchMethodException

    public Object invokeMethod(Object o, String n, Class[] p, Object[] v) throws java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException {
        com.sqs.javatest.health.interfaces.ImService w;
        try {
            w = ((com.sqs.javatest.health.interfaces.ImService) $1);
        } catch (Throwable e) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException(e);
        }
        try {
            if ("getMsg".equals($2) && $3.length == 1) {
                return ($w) w.getMsg((java.lang.String) $4[0]);
            }
            if ("getMsg2".equals($2) && $3.length == 1) {
                return ($w) w.getMsg2((java.lang.String) $4[0]);
            }
        } catch (Throwable e) {
            throw new java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException(e);
        }
        throw new com.alibaba.dubbo.common.bytecode.NoSuchMethodException("Not found method \"" + $2 + "\" in class com.sqs.javatest.health.interfaces.ImService.");
    }

